tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE filaments (
    filament_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    filament_name VARCHAR(50),
    filament_type VARCHAR(50),
    filament_color VARCHAR(30),
    filament_quantity INT
);

CREATE TABLE resins (
    resin_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    resin_name VARCHAR(50),
    resin_type VARCHAR(50),
    resin_color VARCHAR(30),
    resin_quantity INT
);

CREATE TABLE filaments (
    filament_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    material_name VARCHAR(255),
    color VARCHAR(50),
    quantity INT,
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE resins (
    resin_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    material_name VARCHAR(255),
    color VARCHAR(50),
    volume INT,
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE inventory (
    inventory_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    material_name VARCHAR(255),
    type VARCHAR(50),
    quantity INT,
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE filaments (
    filament_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    filament_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT,
    color TEXT,
    material TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE resins (
    resin_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    resin_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    quantity INT,
    color TEXT,
    cured_in_uv BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE prints (
    print_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    filament_id UUID REFERENCES filaments(filament_id),
    resin_id UUID REFERENCES resins(resin_id),
    printer_id UUID REFERENCES printers(printer_id),
    print_duration INTERVAL,
    print_quality TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE filaments (
  filament_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  filament_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  filament_color VARCHAR(50),
  filament_material_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY(filament_material_id) REFERENCES materials(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE resins (
  resin_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  resin_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  resin_color VARCHAR(50),
  resin_material_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY(resin_material_id) REFERENCES materials(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE printers (
  printer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  printer_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  printer_model VARCHAR(50),
  printer_filament_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY(printer_filament_id) REFERENCES filaments(filament_id)
);

CREATE TABLE print_jobs (
  job_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  job_timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  job_printer_id INT,
  job_material_id INT,
  job_quantity INT,
  FOREIGN KEY(job_printer_id) REFERENCES printers(printer_id),
  FOREIGN KEY(job_material_id) REFERENCES materials(material_id)
);
